parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Strut Housing Corrosion and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the front strut housing can cause the strut to break off from the frame, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or wobbles violently
especially at high speeds
and may cause the driver to lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The death wobble or rear sway can cause the vehicle to lose control, especially at high speeds, and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or wobbles violently
especially at high speeds
and may cause the driver to lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Upper and Lower Rear Control Link Arm Bushing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the upper and lower rear control link arm bushings can cause the vehicle to sway excessively, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle sways or wobbles excessively
especially at high speeds
and may cause the driver to lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or bucks
stalls
or fails to move; loud grinding or clunking noises; RPMs jump or stay high; difficulty shifting into gear; vehicle rolls backward freely while in drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transfer case failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or bucks
stalls
or fails to move; loud grinding or clunking noises; difficulty shifting into gear; four-wheel drive system malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Driveshaft failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud clunking noises; difficulty shifting into gear; driveshaft failure makes clunky noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and gearbox issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting into gear; clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; clutch pedal sticks to the floor; vehicle unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Acceleration and Sticking Accelerator Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration and sticking accelerator pedal can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks when accelerating from a stop

causing the vehicle to lurch forward; the pedal sticks at speeds of 50 mph and above; the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly; the pedal feels stuck or catches suddenly; the vehicle jumps forward when the pedal is depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, and loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy; the brakes do not function when applied; the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly; the steering wheel is stiff.
